data.enText: to arrange things or people in a particular way or position

data.chText: 使倾向于；使有意于；使易于
data.enText: to make sb behave in a particular way
a drug that disposes the patient towards sleep

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

data.enText: to get rid of sb/sth that you do not want or cannot keep
the difficulties of disposing of nuclear waste
to deal with a problem, question or threat successfully

data.chText: 这样就似乎把他们的大部分论点都驳倒了。
data.enText: That seems to have disposed of most of their arguments.

data.chText: 她仅用了20分钟就击败了对手。
data.enText: It took her a mere 20 minutes to dispose of her opponent.

example: Your education qualifies you for this job

tr: make receptive or willing towards an action or attitude or belief
example: Their language inclines us to believe them

tr: place or put in a particular order
give, sell, or transfer to another
example: She disposed of her parents' possessions

trans: 丢掉；清除；处理；办妥；处理好；解决
